                    <lb/>busy to write myself. </p>
                <p> I have not yet got your answer about <lb/>my royalties from records and whether
                    you have <lb/>paid (as I <ref target="letter.3149">asked</ref> you previously.)
                    the monthly <lb/>amount to my son <persName key="pers.3281">Georg<del rendition="#s">e</del> Sch.</persName> Would you be <lb/>kind enough to
                    do this as soon as possible. </p>
                <p> Today I want <add place="superlinear">at first</add> to thank you for sending me
                    <lb/>the music I <ref target="letter.3167">ordered</ref>. But I think a number
                    <lb/>of the packages must be delayed, and I hope <lb/>they will arrive soon. </p>
                <p> From the <ref target="document.24093">bills</ref> I saw, I observed to <lb/>my
                    astonishment that you charge me for my own <lb/>works. It was an agreement with
                    Mr. <persName key="pers.1538">Herzka</persName>
                    <lb/>that I get copies without <add place="superlinear">any</add> charge. </p>
                <p> As I am not selling them, it would be <lb/>awkward to me to pay for them. The
                    reason why I <lb/>need them is that I was persuaded by <lb/>requirements of
                    students to make donations of <lb/>my works to a number of public libraries. On
                    <lb/>account of the present depression here, the public <lb/>libraries are not
                    in a position to buy modern music. <lb/>But they assure me that it would
                    stimulate <lb/>musicians to buy my scores if some of them <lb/>are available in
                    libraries. As a proof of this, <lb/>I send you the enclosed newspaper clipping! </p>
                <note place="mBottom" hand="#author">
                    <hi rendition="#circle">over</hi>
                </note>
                <pb n="3" sameAs="#p.1"/>
                <p> By the way, you even charge me for my opera <lb/>
                    <bibl sameAs="werke.65">„VON HEUTE AUF MORGEN“</bibl>, that is my property <lb/>for
                    that I paid not only the printing expenses, but also <lb/>that of the lawsuit I
                    lost. <lb/>Please kindly rectify this matter. </p>
